****************************************************
For installation, we require several third party packages
****************************************************

a) cmake, see
http://www.cmake.org/HTML/Index.html
(used as Makefile generator)


b) umfpack
http://www.cise.ufl.edu/research/sparse/umfpack/
(used as direct sparse solver)


c) metis
http://www-users.cs.umn.edu/~karypis/metis/
(used for optimisation of matrix storage)


****************************************************
Architecture
****************************************************

We require c++ version 11 compilers


****************************************************
Quick Installation
****************************************************

1.) In the Gascoigne directory call the bash script

    sh ./install_gascoigne.sh

****************************************************
Custom Installation
****************************************************

Let <GAS_DIR> be the main directory of Gascoigne 3d

1.) Create a build directory, e.g. and in this directory configure
Gascoigne by

	  mkdir build
	  cd build
	  ccmake <GAS_DIR>

2.) Compile Gascoigne. In the build directory

    	    make

